{"id":10825,"date":"2011-06-20T07:07:03","date_gmt":"2011-06-20T11:07:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/staging.budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/?p=10825"},"modified":"2018-02-13T07:22:39","modified_gmt":"2018-02-13T12:22:39","slug":"rent-a-room-in-a-mansion","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/rent-a-room-in-a-mansion\/","title":{"rendered":"Rent a Room In a Mansion? Okay!"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.smartmoney.com\/spend\/real%20estate\/room-for-rent--in-a-mansion-1297274862469\/\"><img decoding=\"async\" style=\"margin: 0pt 10px 10px 0pt; float: none;\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/mansion-water.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"mansion on water\" width=\"500\" height=\"256\" \/><\/a><br \/>\n<strong>I just read this KILLER article about renting rooms out of mansions!<\/strong> If you&#8217;re subscribed to Smart Money you may have <a href=\"http:\/\/www.smartmoney.com\/spend\/real%20estate\/room-for-rent--in-a-mansion-1297274862469\/\">seen it<\/a>, but in a nutshell it talks about people with freakin&#8217; AWESOME homes who are struggling to keep them up due to the economy, and so they&#8217;re looking for new ways to offset the costs.  The easiest &amp; most obvious of them being to rent out 1 of their billion rooms they have in their palace! :) And when I say palace, I mean just that.  Some of the places featured were insane!  Pools, theaters, top of the line kitchens &#8211; you name it.  One of the families even gives you access to their Mercedes convertible! It&#8217;s pretty dope.<\/p>\n<p><strong>So naturally the first thing I did was try and sneak it by the Mrs. to see what kinda hope, or not, I had of giving this a shot ;)<\/strong> And she actually surprised me a bit and said she&#8217;d be open to it!!  Now, a whole mess of variables would have to line up in order for that to ever become a reality (they&#8217;d have to allow cats, it would have to be within driving distance to her school, we&#8217;d have to have a LOT of privacy, etc) BUT if there&#8217;s a one in a million shot, you better believe I&#8217;m gonna go for it! Haha&#8230; don&#8217;t tell her yet though cuz right now it&#8217;s just a &#8220;crazy idea&#8221; in my head like the rest of them :)<\/p>\n<p>But think about it. How could would that be?  To roll up to a gated mansion w\/ your own room and access to everything you&#8217;d ever need?  For as little as $600 in some cases?? If I were single I&#8217;d take it in a heartbeat.  And even now I&#8217;m obviously still for it, haha&#8230; but then again I&#8217;m still in that <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/2009\/08\/living-minimalist-lifestyle-is-it\/\">minimalism phase<\/a> where I think I&#8217;d be much happier with a smaller place w\/ less stuff.  (smaller as in &#8220;our&#8221; section &#8211; I&#8217;m totally cool living on palace grounds as long as I&#8217;m just responsible for a small patch of it!).<\/p>\n<p><strong>It&#8217;ll probably never happen, but it&#8217;s ideas like this that REALLY get my excitement going.<\/strong> Just for the fact there are OTHER ways to live out there other than the normal &#8220;home owner&#8221; route.  I don&#8217;t know if I&#8217;ve ever told you or not before, but I&#8217;m so <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/2010\/02\/we-got-milked-for-24000-last-year-how\/\">over my house<\/a>!!! ;) Haha&#8230;. so that&#8217;s what I&#8217;m dreaming up over here in my head. What do you guys think about that?  <em><strong>Could you ever see yourself trying it out for a year or two?<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n<p>If I find a way to pull it off I&#8217;ll let you know, but either way Operation &#8220;Find a new place to live&#8221; is definitely back in the works. Anyone wanna buy a sexy townhouse for $300,000? :)<\/p>\n<p>&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;<br \/>\n<em>(Photo by Christopher Gosselin)<\/em><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendere